New Records: England inflicted Oman's lowest completed total in T20s, and the lowest England have ever inflicted on anybody in a T20
Key Match Events: England beat Oman by eight wickets with 101 balls to spare
Mark Wood took 3 wickets for 12 runs
Pre-Game Insights: England's next game is against Namibia on Saturday
England need to beat Namibia and Scotland lose to Australia to scrape through to the Super 8s
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler said the tone was set by the bowlers, and they restricted Oman and knocked them off
Mark Wood said they had a point to prove and the pitch was extra bouncey
Miscellaneous Highlights: The player of the match is Adil Rashid
England's net run rate rose from -1.80 to +3.08
